Simulation data vector used in Joachimi (2017), MNRAS, 466, 83

The files are of the form

xi_athena_final_shrinkage_lognormal_2zbin_shapenoise_0[i]_0[j]_[k].dat

where

i,j in [1,2]  and i<=j

and

k in [0001;2000]

i,j denote the unique combination of redshift bins (3 combinations in this case). k runs over the noise realisation of the data vector.

The data vector for any given realisation can be assembled as follows:
1. In each file extract the 2nd (xi_+) and 3rd (xi_-) columns and concatenate. Two correlation functions a 20 angular bin measurements -> size 40.
2. Then concatenate the vectors from (1.) for different redshift bins in the order 01_01, 01_02, 02_02. 3 vectors a 40 elements -> size 120.


When using this data please cite the reference given above and refer to their Section 4 for details on the simulations and measurements done on them.

